org.apache.ignite.cache.eviction.random

Class RandomEvictionPolicy<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ignite.cache.eviction.random.RandomEvictionPolicy<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Externalizable, Serializable, EvictionPolicy<K,V>, RandomEvictionPolicyMBean

    public class RandomEvictionPolicy<K,V>
extends Object
implements EvictionPolicy<K,V>, RandomEvictionPolicyMBean, Externalizable
    Cache eviction policy which will select random cache entry for eviction if cache size exceeds the getMaxSize() parameter. This implementation is extremely light weight, lock-free, and does not create any data structures to maintain any order for eviction.

    Random eviction will provide the best performance over any key queue in which every key has the same probability of being accessed.
